                    </p>
                    <p>
                        I wrote my first line of code in a grade 10 computer class, using Visual Basic to create my first application: a "Hello World" console line (of course). I would later create hang-man games and
                        calculators, and would discover during that class a passion for writing software.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        After high school I completed a bachelor of arts degree with a major in music. Although coding and conducting may seem like unrelated fields, I found the mathematics of music theory to be
                        fascinating. I spent my days in music classes while learning C# and creating games in the Unity3D game engine on evenings and weekends.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        I have since moved from my home on the Canadian prairies to Montreal and expanded my software development experience from Unity games to WPF and UWP applications using the .NET Framework.
